        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 4:19PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Beechwood Hills, or
near Athens, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 30 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Lightning will be a hazard for anyone outdoors. Seek
shelter to remain safe.

Locations impacted include...
Watkinsville, Athens, Winterville, Colbert, Arnoldsville, Hull,
Athens-Clarke County, Whitehall, Westgate Park, James Holland Youth
Sports Cmpx, Diamond Hill, Beechwood Hills, Sandy Creek Recreation
Area, Oconee Heights, Barretts Mill, Dunlap, State Botanical Garden
Of Ga, and Neese.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
